## Conclusion for #58 root-cause

The iterative `mulDivFUIterative` FSM in
`src/Riski5/Core/FU/MulDiv.hs` is **not** robust to register
initialization assumptions. Three different backends start the
FSM in three different states and produce three different
divergence cadences. The Clash sim's NFData defaults happen to
work for both 10 iters in pure-Haskell AND 9 iters when Quartus
infers similar power-up values; Verilator's undefined-init does
not. The silicon "10th-iter fail" is the same bug, just
expressed at a different ordinal because Quartus partially
matches Clash sim's defaults but not perfectly.

Fix path: explicit reset values on the FSM's mealy state
register (single-line Clash change).
